\sectd\sbknone\colsx360\pgncont\ltrsect
\pard\plain\ltrpar\qc\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs32\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Young Mr. Truman and His Music}{\s28\f0\fs32\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\qc\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs32\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\qc\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch by Jim U\uc1\u8217\'92Ren}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\qc\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\qc\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs20\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Initial Draft}{\s28\f0\fs20\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs20\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch \uc0\u-257 }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\b\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch A young man on a mission}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\line }{\s28\f0\fs24\b\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch A young Harry Truman hurries down the sidewalk with a rolled bundle tucked under one arm. His closest friend, Charlie, catches a glimpse of Harry as he hurries away from the neighborhood. Being his best, Charlie isn't about to deride his friend for disappearing twice a week after school while the rest of the neighborhood gang is out playing. This boy is obviously is a 'young man on a mission' and he wasn't afraid of being different and doing things differently from his neighborhood chums.  Young Harry was already his own man. }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch As most boys in their early years - - they have no idea what life has in store for them. So it was with young Harry.\~\~ Little did he\~ know that in fifty years he will he would be the leader of the most powerful nation on the planet, immersed in a global global conflict fighting for its very existence.\~\~}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch But at this moment, at the age of 10, young Harry is focused on his first passion - - music. And today he must catch the electric trolley to Kansas City. There his piano teacher,  Grace White teaches piano out of her home at 27th and Brooklyn. It is a large two story brick house with a Steinway grand piano in spacious front parlor. Twice a week young Harry would make the trip to have Mrs. White drill him on the fundamentals of proper piano. And Harry took to it like a fish to water. So much that Harry was considered her best student.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The trolley ride from Independence to Kansas City did more than just transport him from his home to his piano lessons.  It took him into a completely different world. }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Though the trips to Mrs. Whites were about music, there were so many things a young Harry Truman was exposed to beyond the piano lessons in Mrs. Whites parlor.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch First there was the simple fact that Harry was making a voyage from Antebellum Independence into the heart of \uc1\u8220\'93Yankee Town\uc1\u8221\'94.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Next there was the fact that Harry was being taught piano by a European trained pianist who would have included personal and historical stories about the context of the music he was learning.  And as the young boy who was fascinated with history, these anecdotes would be would ad texture to the fabric of knowledge young Harry was building.  This would have opened doors in young Harry\uc1\u8217\'92s mind to a world much larger, complex and varied than what he experienced in Independence.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Harry at a young age was building a bridge in his mind between the two sides that just thirty years prior were trying to tear the country apart. }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch And then at the end of each lesson, young Harry would walk the five block back the Winner\uc1\u8217\'92s Electric Trolley Line and return to his family in Independence.  No doubt Harry\uc1\u8217\'92s parents, John and Mary Truman, liked what they saw in young Harry as he returned from is trips into Kansas City because they paid for those lessons and the trolley tolls for six years.   They probably liked how Harry would fill the house with music playing on the family\uc1\u8217\'92s Kinball piano.  A piano would provide a form of entertainment for a family in an age did not have radio, television or any of the entertainment sources we take for granted today.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The sights and sounds of that trolley ride were trans-formative for young Harry. And in Mrs Whites home Harry was again transported into a world of music and culture that must have seemed thousands of miles from his neighborhood in Independence. }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Not that Independence was in anyway backward, in fact just opposite. It was known as town of culture and thinkers with with its share of world travelers. But Independence had strong Southern roots that differentiated it from\~Kansas City which }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\b\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The ride on the Winner Line}{\s28\f0\fs24\b\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\b\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\b\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\b\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\b\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The lessons with Mrs. White}{\s28\f0\fs24\b\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\b\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Grace White was not your average piano teacher.  She was trained in Europe by, Theodore Leschetizky, a prominent teacher of the time.   Leschetizky taught scores of prominent musicians, most notably Ignacy Jan Paderewski,  a popular piano virtuoso in the 1890s and early 1900s. }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The twice weekly voyages to his piano lessons would clearly be  trans-formative events for a young Harry Truman.  }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Harry received instruction from Mrs. White on a Steinway concert grand piano in the spacious front parlor of the White residence at 27th and Brooklyn in what was then the eastern edge of Kansas City.  It must have been a special treat for young Harry to play on a Steinway Grand.   The magnificent voice of a concert grand would have been very different than the Kimbal upright which was in the Truman home in Independence.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch [Conclusion]}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch It\uc1\u8217\'92s impossible to know the precise effect music had on a young Mr. Truman.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Later in life, music would continue to connect Harry Truman in ways the young man could scarcely imagine.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0\par}